# Web Component Decomposition

## Page file layout (all routes)

Every route page lives under its own directory, not as a loose `*-page.tsx` in `pages/`:

- `apps/web/src/pages/<route-folder>/<name>-page.tsx` — route component (e.g. `home/home-page.tsx`, `game-detail/game-detail-page.tsx`).
- `apps/web/src/pages/<route-folder>/<name>-page.module.scss` — styles for that page shell.
- Optional `apps/web/src/pages/<route-folder>/components/<piece>/<piece>.tsx` + `<piece>.module.scss` when the page is split (see games list).

Import app code from the page file with `../../api`, `../../lib`, etc. Router imports use `./pages/<route-folder>/<name>-page`.

Prefer small components scoped to one UI responsibility (for example: `filters-panel`, `game-card`, `pagination`).

When a file starts mixing search/filter logic, card rendering, and toolbar/layout code, extract focused components before adding new behavior.

Aim for composition over deeply nested JSX in one file:

- Keep container/route components focused on data loading, URL state, and orchestration.
- Move presentational sections into dedicated components with typed props.
- Extract reusable interactions (dropdowns, sliders, segmented controls) into `components/ui` or feature-level components.

Favor reuse over duplication:

- Reuse existing components and style tokens before creating new variants.
- When two routes share the same pattern, extract a common component/hook instead of copy-pasting.

Keep extracted components close to feature usage:

- One folder per route under `apps/web/src/pages/<route-name>/`: the page entry file (for example `games-list-page.tsx`), its page shell `*.module.scss` (layout, route chrome), and a `components/` folder for pieces used only on that page.
- Co-locate styles with each page-local component: one folder per component, for example `components/catalog-game-card/catalog-game-card.tsx` + `catalog-game-card.module.scss` (same basename). Only styles that truly belong to the route shell stay on the page SCSS module.
- Highly reusable, design-system style pieces belong in `apps/web/src/components/ui/` (or other shared `components/` subtrees when used across multiple features).
- Promote a page-local component to shared `components/` only when a second feature needs it.
